{"title_page": "Amy Feldman", "text_new": "{{Short description|American painter}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Amy Feldman\n| image         = \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{birth year and age|1981}}\n| birth_place   = [[New Windsor, New York]]\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[United States|American]]\n| field         = [[Painting]]\n| training      = \n| movement      = \n| works         = \n| patrons       = \n| influenced by = \n| influenced    =\n| awards        = \n}}'''Amy Feldman''' (born 1981) is an American [[abstract art|abstract painter]] from [[New York (state)|New York]].\n\n== Education ==\nAmy Feldman received a BFA in painting from the [[Rhode Island School of Design]] in [[Providence, Rhode Island]] in 2003.  Her honors concentration was in [[art history]], [[Aesthetics|theory]], and [[Art criticism|criticism]]. She then attended [[Rutgers University]] in New Brunswick, New Jersey where she received an MFA in Painting in 2008.  She subsequently attended the [[Skowhegan School of Painting and Sculpture]] for a nine-week residency in 2009.\n\n==Work==\nFeldman's work has been shown in galleries and museums since 2008. Her work is planned, and spontaneously painted with loosely geometric, graphic gestures in whites to dark grays on various whites to gray grounds.<ref>[https://archives.sfweekly.com/sanfrancisco/new-western-vistas/Content?oid=2825742 ''Jonathan Curiel, Amy Feldman's New Western Vistas, The San Francisco Weekly, Mar 20, 2013'']</ref> The stark contrast between figure and ground in Feldman's paintings is initially arresting, then subsequently complicated, exploratory, and meditative.<ref>[http://amyfeldmanstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/new_york_catalog_kunstmuseum_bonn.pdf''Christoph Schreier, New York Painting, Kunstmuseum Bonn, Hirmer Publishers, 2015({{ISBN|3777424196}}, {{ISBN|978-3777424194}})'']</ref> [[File:Cold Century.jpg|thumb|Cold Century, 2015, acrylic on canvas, 79 x 79 inches]] Feldman's bold, urgent, and large scale abstract paintings are often anthropomorphic and darkly humorous with psychologically charged imagery.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/13/arts/design/amy-feldman-dark-selects.html ''Roberta Smith, Art in Review, Amy Feldman: Dark Selects, The New York Times, July 13, 2012'']</ref><ref>[http://www.artinamericamagazine.com/reviews/amy-feldman/ ''Amanda Palmer, Amy Feldman: Blackston, Art in America, Issue No. 9, pp. 174\u2013175, October 2012'']</ref><ref>[https://www.taschen.com/pages/en/catalogue/music/all/03430/facts.art_record_covers.htm/ ''Francesco Spampinato, \"Art Record Covers\", Taschen, 2017 ({{ISBN|978-3836540292}})'']</ref><ref>[http://abar.net/snow.pdf ''Anthony Barnett\u00a0and Ian Brinton, \"Snow lit rev, no. 6\", Allardyce, Barnett, Publishers, April 30, 2018 ({{ISBN|0907954561}}, {{ISBN|978-0907954569}})'']</ref> Her stripped down abstract sign system addresses, among other things, [[topology]], [[morphology (biology)|morphology]], and the perception and transmission of [[information theory|information]]. Feldman's artistic influences range from [[Cubism]] to the works of [[Henri Matisse]],<ref>[http://thesilo.raphaelrubinstein.com/artists/matisse-etc-part-2''Raphael Rubinstein, \"Matisse Etc. (part 2)\", The Silo, December 1, 2014'']</ref> [[Jean Arp]], [[Ellsworth Kelly]], [[Shirley Jaffe (artist)|Shirley Jaffe]], [[Mary Heilmann]]<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/art/article/Amy-Feldman-melds-poise-rough-edges-4333900.php''Nirmala Nataraj, \"Amy Feldman Melds Poise, Rough Edges\", The San Francisco Chronicle, March 6, 2013'']</ref> and [[Robert Ryman]].<ref>[http://www.phaidon.com/store/art/robert-ryman-9780714849348/''Vittorio Colaizzi, \"Robert Ryman\", Phaidon Press, September 4, 2017 ({{ISBN|0714849340}}, {{ISBN|978-0714849348}})'']</ref>\n\nFeldman is represented by [https://andersenscontemporary.dk/artists/52819/amy-feldman/works/ ''Andersens Contemporary''] in [[Copenhagen]], [https://www.annabohmangallery.com/amy-feldman-works ''Anna Bohman Gallery''] in [[Stockholm]], [https://www.blainsouthern.com/artists/amy-feldman ''Blain|Southern''] in [[Berlin]] and [[London]], [http://www.brandnew-gallery.com/Software/artist_mainC.php?artist=252 ''Brand New Gallery''] in [[Milan]], [http://www.galeriahilariogalguera.com/nueva/index.php?id=370 ''Galer\u00eda Hilario Galguera''] in [[Mexico City]] and [http://www.ratio3.org/artists/amy-feldman ''Ratio 3''] in [[San Francisco]].\n\nFeldman's work is in the permanent collections of the [[Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago|Museum of Contemporary Art]]<ref>[http://www.mcachicago.org/''Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago, IL'']</ref> in [[Chicago]], the [[Sheldon Museum of Art]]<ref>[http://sheldonartmuseum.org/''Sheldon Museum of Art, Lincoln, NE'']</ref> in [[Lincoln, Nebraska]], the Hall Art Foundation | Schloss Derneburg Museum<ref>[http://www.hallartfoundation.org/location/schloss-derneburg ''Schloss Derneburg Museum, Derneberg, Germany'']</ref> in [[Holle|Derneburg, Germany]], and the Vanhaerents Art Collection<ref>[https://vanhaerentsartcollection.com''Vanhaerents Art Collection, Brussels, Belgium'']</ref> in [[Brussels, Belgium]]. She lives and works in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City|New York]].\n\n== Exhibitions ==\n;Solo exhibitions\n*[https://www.annabohmangallery.com/amy-feldman-2018 ''Counter Ground, ANNAELLE Gallery, Stockholm, Sweden, 2018'']\n*[http://www.jamescohan.com/exhibitions/amy-feldman''Nerve Reserve, James Cohan Gallery, New York City, New York, 2017'']\n*[http://www.blainsouthern.com/exhibitions/2017/breath-myth/''Breath Myth, Blain|Southern, Berlin, Germany, 2017'']\n*[http://www.ratio3.org/exhibitions/amy-feldman-psyche-shade''Psyche Shade, Ratio 3, San Francisco, California, 2016'']\n*[http://www.corbettvsdempsey.com/2016/04/06/amy-feldman/''Good Gloom, Corbett vs. Dempsey, Chicago, Illinois, 2016'']\n*[http://www.brandnew-gallery.com/Software/exhib_mainC.php?exhib=329''Moon Decorum, Brand New Gallery, Milan, Italy, 2015'']\n*[https://www.annabohmangallery.com/amy-feldman-2015''Trice Electric, ANNAELLE Gallery, Stockholm, Sweden, 2015'']\n*''Mirror Cool, Reynolds Gallery, Richmond, Virginia, 2015''\n*[http://blackstongallery.com/artist.php?id=73&show_id=208''High Sign, Blackston Gallery, New York City, New York, 2014'']\n*[http://www.sorrywereclosed.com/en/expositions/presentation/51/amy-feldman''Gray Area, Sorry, We're Closed Gallery, Brussels, Belgium, 2014'']\n*[https://www.annabohmangallery.com/amy-feldman-2013''Stark Types, ANNAELLE Gallery, Stockholm, Sweden, 2013'']\n*[http://www.gregorylindgallery.com/exhibitions/2013/feldman/''Raw Graces, Gregory Lind Gallery, San Francisco, California, 2013'']\n;\n;Selected group exhibitions\n*[http://39greatjones.com/gallery_entry/amy-feldman/ ''Mutual Ritual, 39 Great Jones, New York, NY, curated by Ugo Rondinone, 2019'']\n*[http://www.hallartfoundation.org/exhibition/this-and-that-some-recent-acquisitions/artworks/thumbnails ''This and That: Some Recent Acquisitions, Hall Art Foundation | Schloss Derneburg Museum, Derneburg, Germany, 2018'']\n*[http://www.sheldonartmuseum.org/exhibitions/nonobjectives''nonObjectives, Sheldon Museum of Art, Lincoln, NE, curated by Walter Mason, 2017'']\n*[https://www.albertbaronian.com/exhibitions/artemisia-group-show-2017/''Artemisia, Albert Baronian, Brussels, Belgium, 2017'']\n*[http://www.blainsouthern.com/exhibitions/2017/playground-structure''Playground Structure, Blain|Southern, London, UK, 2017'']\n*''Quicktime, University of the Arts, Philadelphia, PA, 2017''\n*[http://invisible-exports.com/exhibitions/heartbreak-hotel/''Heartbreak Hotel, Invisible Exports, New York, NY, 2017'']\n*[https://mcachicago.org/Exhibitions/2016/Riot-Grrrls''MCA DNA: Riot Grrrls, Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago, Illinois, curated by Michael Darling, 2016-2017'']\n*[http://www.jackhanley.com/exhibitions/the-congregation''The Congregation, Jack Hanley Gallery